does WAF  DDoS    SSL are not cloudfront features right?

Yes! Exactly right. Good catch!
They are separate AWS services — not CloudFront features:

CloudFront alone:
  ✅ CDN                → YES built in to CloudFront
  ❌ WAF                → separate AWS WAF service
  ❌ DDoS               → separate AWS Shield service
  ❌ SSL                → separate AWS ACM service

But they all INTEGRATE with CloudFront:

CloudFront distribution
  ├── attaches AWS WAF    ← you enable separately
  ├── attaches AWS Shield ← automatically on CloudFront
  └── attaches AWS ACM    ← you attach certificate

Each service explained:
AWS CloudFront:

What it does:  CDN only
               caches content at edge locations
               reduces latency for global users
Standalone:    ✅ yes works alone

AWS WAF:

What it does:  Web Application Firewall
               blocks SQL injection, XSS, bots
               custom rules
Standalone:    ✅ yes works alone
               attaches to CloudFront, ALB, API Gateway

AWS Shield:

What it does:  DDoS protection
Tiers:
  Shield Standard → ✅ FREE, automatic on all AWS resources
  Shield Advanced → 💸 paid, enhanced protection
Standalone:    ✅ automatic, no setup needed

AWS ACM:

What it does:  SSL/TLS certificate management
               FREE certificates
               auto renewal
Standalone:    ✅ yes works alone
               attaches to CloudFront, ALB, API Gateway

Correct way to say it:

❌ Wrong:
"CloudFront has WAF, DDoS, SSL"

✅ Correct:
"CloudFront integrates with
  AWS WAF for web filtering
  AWS Shield for DDoS protection
  AWS ACM for SSL certificates"












